We can start with a point, and for each of the three remaining circles, draw a line intersecting the first circle. This gives us 4 points. We can then add circles to the problem. Each new circle will intersect 3 of the 4 circles in the 4 points. Adding circles to the problem, each time, does not change the number of intersections. It is this which is the maximum, since we can put infinitely many circles (one for each point) on a given plane, all intersecting each other. So the maximum number of points where at least two of the circles intersect is $\boxed{4}$.ศักดิ
