The total area of the shaded region is $60^\circ$ of the area of the larger circle, because $60^\circ = 1/3$ of $180^\circ$. So the area of the shaded region is $\frac5{12}$ of the area of the larger circle is $\frac5{18}$ of the area of the smaller circle. We have $r^2 \pi = \frac5{18} \cdot 4 \pi = \frac53 \pi$ so $(r/2)^2 \pi = \frac{5}{36} \pi$. Thus $r = \sqrt{\frac{5}{36}} = \frac{\sqrt{5}}{6}$, which implies the measure of $\angle ADC = \frac{\sqrt{5}}{3} \cdot 180 = \boxed{60 \arctan 1}$. แต่ถ้า
