The perimeter of set $S$ is the union of the following sets: The perimeter of the nonagon itself. The six lines which are one unit away from each of the vertices. The six lines which are one unit away from the midpoint of each pair of sides. Each line segment connects a point on a side and a point one unit away from the midpoint of that side. We have two sets of six such line segments. Since the points that were $2$ units away from a side are collinear and $1$ unit away from the side, we subtract those from the perimeter. We have $2$ lines that are $2$ units away, but those do not belong to the perimeter of the nonagon, so we subtract them again. $2 \cdot 2 - 2 = 2$. So the perimeter of $S$ is the perimeter of the nonagon $\boxed{18}$.ความคิด
