Also, we know that $a \ge 3,$ because we have a triangle with sides $2,1,1,$ so $a \ge 3.$ Similarly, we have $b \ge 2.$

Now consider the inequality $1 \ge c + 1 - (a + b).$ This inequality represents a line in the $a,$ $b,$ $c$ plane.

Hence, we must consider three cases:

\begin{align*}
0 \le a, &\le b, \\
a, &\le b \le c, \\
a \le b \le c \le 3.
\end{align*}

For $0 \le a, \le b,$ the answer is
