For a second way of looking at this problem, notice that the set of all odd prime numbers less than 30 is the set of all odd prime numbers up to 19, so its cardinality is the same as the cardinality of the set of all odd numbers up to 19. Is there a one-to-one correspondence between this set and the set of all odd numbers up to 19? Yes, every number of the set of all odd numbers up to 19 can be mapped to a unique odd number greater than 0 by simply taking the number itself. Thus the two sets have the same cardinality, and there is just $\boxed{1}$ element in their intersection.เป็นเรื่อง
